{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3ee9c9a-7140-4ec1-a36c-dc45a6f367f2","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard `ContentPage` property in .NET MAUI — you need platform-specific approaches for each OS:\n\n**iOS** — Add the platform-specific namespace and disable safe area insets:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\">\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Android** — Enable edge-to-edge in your `MainActivity.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    if (Window != null)\n    {\n        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n> **Note:** On Android 15+ (which .NET 10 targets), edge-to-edge is the default, so the `MainActivity` change may already be handled — but you still need `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on iOS.\n\nAlso make sure `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"` is set on your `Image` so it actually fills the available space rather than letterboxing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9373d4f8-4947-4a37-88ee-43ebee72cab1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about making an image go edge-to-edge in a .NET MAUI app, going behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still have padding.\n\nThis is a .NET MAUI question about ignoring safe areas for full-screen/edge-to-edge content. Let me think about what's needed:\n\nIn .NET MAUI, `SafeAreaEdges` is an iOS-specific concept. Setting `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the page tells it not to automatically adjust for safe areas on iOS. But there are a few things the user might be missing:\n\n\nOn iOS specifically, I need to use the platform-specific property `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` to actually allow content to extend behind the status and navigation bars. The `SafeAreaEdges` property alone might not be enough depending on the MAUI version. For Android, I need to handle edge-to-edge display configuration, which in newer MAUI versions (especially .NET 9+) has better built-in support, though older Android versions may require explicit opt-in through platform-specific code. Writing platform-specific configuration...","outputTokens":1566,"requestId":"DBCD:852E1:107AE5:14BB30:69F54DF2"},"id":"82e8a8fd-56c7-4902-87ed-287552989df6","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:06:24.372Z","parentId":"aad2c831-c999-457f-a4e4-bfe6eeb46f34"}
